# CRM Project

Standalone CRM, forked from Offerio — built for a single client.

## Stack
- Frontend: Vite + React SPA (TypeScript strict)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- Backend: Supabase self-hosted (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- Deployment: Coolify / Hetzner VPS

## Architecture
- **Single tenant** — one client, one database
- Supabase via SSH tunnel → localhost:5433
- No SSR, no Next.js, no custom backend
- All DB calls via `supabase.from()`

## Folder Structure
```
src/
  components/   # Reusable UI components (PascalCase)
  pages/        # Page-level components
  hooks/        # Custom React hooks
  lib/          # Supabase client, helpers (camelCase)
  types/        # TypeScript type definitions
  utils/        # Pure utility functions
```

## NEVER do this
- NO Stripe or payment logic
- NO multi-tenant logic
- NO `console.log` in production — use proper error handling
- NO hardcoded credentials or API keys
- NO barrel exports (`index.ts` re-exports)
- NO `any` types
